The paper discusses data replication and deployment of local SPARQL endpoints, which are topics related to database systems (cs.DB). The proposed approach, Fedra, involves using provenance and views to reduce the number of selected endpoints while satisfying user divergence requirements, which is a technique commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and deep learning (cs.DL). The paper also discusses query processing strategies, which is a topic related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and software engineering (cs.SE).
